==English==
===Noun===
'''[[dog]] [[year]]''' (''plural:'' '''[[dog years]]''')

# {{informal}} A period of time in the life of dogs, defined such that the average life expectancy of a dog in dog years is numerically equivalent to the average life expectancy of a human. A 4 year old dog is about as mature as a human of 28 to 30 years. A 5 year old dog is about as mature as a human of 33 to 35 years.